properties.inscription: Anne Frank has served as an inspiration to millions around the world and her life warns us of the dangers of intolerance. This tree is dedicated as a place to reflect on all the children who have died owing to the wars and persecution in the last century,
properties.name: Anne Frank's Tree

properties.description: Nelson Mandela first visited the Royal Parks on a bright summer's morning in July 1996. During this visit Manela planted a Plane tree. Nelson Mandela called the tree 'symbolic' and added, "I wish I had the resources to come and water it every week."
properties.fixme: Not aware of exact location, pls survey and move to exact location.
properties.name: The Mandela Tree
